\title{The Stone adjunction}
\date{2023-09-07}
\author{samson-abramsky}
\author{achim-jung}

\def\Top{\mathbf{Top}}
\def\Frm{\mathbf{Frm}}
\def\Pt{\mathsf{Pt}}

\import{axt-000M}

\p{
  The Stone adjunction is the one formed by the [open set functor](axt-000M)
  #{\OO : \Top \to \Frm} and the [point functor](axt-000N) #{\Pt : \Frm \to
  \Top}.
}

\p{
  Adapted by Ayberk Tosun from [the handbook chapter of Abramsky and
  Jung](abramsky-jung-domain-theory-1995).
}
